Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,[Bakuman Episode 16 Translation by Kewl0210]
Comment: 0,0:00:00.11,0:00:00.11,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,{Eyecatch}
Comment: 0,0:00:00.11,0:00:00.11,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{Ending}
Comment: 0,0:00:00.11,0:00:02.11,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,
Comment: 0,0:00:00.11,0:00:02.11,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,

Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.09,0:00:06.94,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro! So Miho's having her debut as a seiyuu, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.11,0:00:09.07,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It's still just a small part.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.51,0:00:11.86,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,He's just being shy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.76,0:00:14.50,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,But it's amazing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.50,0:00:16.46,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if you and Takagi make an anime,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.46,0:00:18.36,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,then you can use Miho for the heroine and get married, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.36,0:00:20.07,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.07,0:00:21.53,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.53,0:00:23.75,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,You can't get an anime adaptation that easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.05,0:00:27.51,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't think Azuki will be able to play the part... 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.51,0:00:29.29,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,if she doesn't get into the position where she can be a heroine. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.24,0:00:32.00,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Why is he being so cool and collected about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.00,0:00:32.92,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,He's that kind of character.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.86,0:00:37.11,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, how about the three of us watch it together when it airs?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.11,0:00:38.57,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It's late at night, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.57,0:00:39.70,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.70,0:00:42.22,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just tell my parents I'm watching it with some friends since Miho's in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.22,0:00:43.75,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,With guy friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.75,0:00:45.64,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I won't tell them that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.39,0:00:48.69,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I'd rather watch it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.17,0:00:52.48,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,R–Really? Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.48,0:00:54.66,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we're heading to the workplace, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.45,0:00:56.16,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.77,0:00:59.87,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is it okay if I watch it with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.87,0:01:00.91,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.40,0:01:02.94,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Sei Visual. {Seiyijiyo.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.94,0:01:04.97,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Azuki becoming a seiyuu...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.97,0:01:06.96,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,and our dream of getting an anime involve me too, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.19,0:01:09.67,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Mm, I guess they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.82,0:01:13.46,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,So, you wanna watch it together at the workplace?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.46,0:01:15.42,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.15,0:01:20.91,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I really want to get an anime before Azuki becomes the heroine for another anime...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:21.89,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.76,0:01:25.69,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Azuki's been our heroine ever since middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.40,0:01:27.84,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Our?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.84,0:01:29.06,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Is that going too far?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.37,0:01:31.52,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Then she's your heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.30,0:01:34.83,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,And my heroine's... Miyoshi?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.83,0:01:35.68,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,You upset about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.68,0:01:37.64,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm totally fine with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.64,0:01:39.64,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,{Opening}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.52,0:03:09.30,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,A heroine, someone who would be liked by everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.30,0:03:11.05,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think this way is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.21,0:03:16.36,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! Since "Futatsu no Chikyuu" and "Kane to Chie" both had dramatic tones to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.36,0:03:18.43,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I can't draw a cute girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.43,0:03:19.54,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you just do it like that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.54,0:03:22.26,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,You know, like when you drew Azuki in your notebook during the third year of middle school?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.90,0:03:24.26,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,N–No good?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.34,0:03:28.79,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just saying, that wasn't a dramatic kind of thing, it was super cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.96,0:03:36.19,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, I've heard of a bunch of times where mangakas drew their own ideal girl as the heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.08,0:03:40.65,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, awesome! I can draw cute really easily! {QC: It seems really odd when the noun after "cute" isn't there...}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.13,0:03:42.59,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.59,0:03:45.91,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,If there aren't any problems with them, make a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.62,0:03:49.50,TL Notes,TL Note,0000,0000,0000,,TL Note: Watashi no Angel = My Angel
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.62,0:03:49.50,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,An angel for a protagonist, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.50,0:03:51.62,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Pirates, ninjas, shinigami, youkai... {perhaps a TL note? 'Youkai are Japanese folk creatures/ghosts'}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.23,0:03:53.97,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Those sort of things are done all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.97,0:03:57.46,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,but I've never seen something in Jack with an angel for a protagonist.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.46,0:03:59.84,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,And if you make it a cool-looking angel, it'll be popular with girls too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.96,0:04:03.72,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,"Hanasaka Tenshi Tenten-kun" had one, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.72,0:04:06.39,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... but that was a gag manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.13,0:04:08.51,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I really liked it as a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.00,0:04:11.78,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Which means this could be popular with kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.78,0:04:16.90,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Well, if you look for manga with angels as protagonists, you could probably find a bunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.90,0:04:20.15,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay. If you're afraid it overlaps with one too much, then I won't draw any more. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.79,0:04:23.31,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,You have an angel suddenly killing someone, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.31,0:04:24.11,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,That's a bad angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.79,0:04:27.74,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,The angels' mission is to deliver dead humans to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.68,0:04:31.02,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,But there are some angels that come down to earth in swarms to deceive and kill humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.02,0:04:32.37,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,in order to earn more points. {Split/shorten, KmE: Splitted the line}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.44,0:04:36.71,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,In order to stop them, the angel of justice swoops down to the human world!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.79,0:04:41.09,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,He falls in love with a girl and they fight the evil angels.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.79,0:04:43.63,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,And the end will be emotionally moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.10,0:04:46.10,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I'm confident about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.10,0:04:48.27,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.27,0:04:51.51,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,This really fulfills the conditions Hattori-san gave us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.08,0:04:56.69,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It's Hattori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.09,0:04:59.40,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, it's Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.13,0:05:04.78,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I know this is sudden, but do you know about the Gold Future Cup?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.78,0:05:06.58,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.58,0:05:08.23,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,They held it last year too, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.23,0:05:10.58,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,That one where newcomers compete with one-shots?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.58,0:05:11.99,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they have it this year too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.63,0:05:15.00,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to try submitting a name...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.00,0:05:17.74,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,in order to gain some achievements before the next issue of NEXT!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.74,0:05:18.83,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.22,0:05:21.34,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,The Gold Future Cup? We'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.34,0:05:22.51,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,We're drawing a good one right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.26,0:05:25.39,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Only four or five works are actually run,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.39,0:05:28.29,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,but I think about twenty names get sent around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.29,0:05:32.93,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,However, the deadline is June 25th, so there's not much time—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.46,0:05:32.56,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.56,0:05:34.39,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have it done with time to spare!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.95,0:05:37.27,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,This is a great chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.27,0:05:38.04,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.04,0:05:39.60,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,If we get first in the Gold Future,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.60,0:05:40.52,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,serialization won't be just a dream anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.11,0:05:42.90,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,We'll definitely make it happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.90,0:05:44.23,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It will be fine, even if it needs fixes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.23,0:05:46.57,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Let's bring in the name three days before the deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.57,0:05:47.22,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.53,0:05:53.25,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,For the angel protagonist, I don't think he should have clothes exactly like a human's.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.25,0:05:57.82,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're right. The readers need to be able to differentiate between angels and humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.82,0:06:00.25,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi! Mashiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.78,0:06:03.02,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I got some tickets to a movie!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.02,0:06:04.61,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,How about the three of us go after school?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.61,0:06:07.45,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, we've got to finish a manuscript in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.99,0:06:09.05,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.05,0:06:10.51,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,You always have them with wings in this name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.93,0:06:14.18,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess they can show them to the humans that find out they're angels,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.18,0:06:15.64,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,but typically they should hide them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.89,0:06:18.89,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.71,0:06:21.44,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,She has lessons today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.08,0:06:26.28,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Why does everybody else have a dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.98,0:06:30.03,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I want a dream too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.96,0:06:33.28,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.40,0:06:38.71,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,You've got everything I said was necessary for a battle manga in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.33,0:06:41.07,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,And it feels natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.07,0:06:43.73,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,You're even more skilled than I thought, Takagi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.73,0:06:47.42,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I didn't think you'd be able to get this far drawing battle manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.03,0:06:48.97,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.97,0:06:50.84,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.84,0:06:51.83,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.83,0:06:55.96,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I'm extremely limited in the advice I can give as an editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.96,0:07:00.58,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,It's very important for mangakas to be able to do more than what their editors tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.58,0:07:01.49,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.49,0:07:04.40,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes. I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.40,0:07:07.69,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)}Editors can't make stories that they can be sure will sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.20,0:07:10.72,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)}And though this sounds extreme, if we could, we'd just draw them ourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.14,0:07:14.28,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,A mangaka has to surpass his editor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.42,0:07:20.93,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,U–Um, are you saying that this name isn't any good after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.61,0:07:24.09,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... Sorry, that's not what I meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.09,0:07:26.18,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying that what you have at this point is good, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.18,0:07:29.48,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want you to just aim higher,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.48,0:07:32.75,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I'd also like you to do something that would surprise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.75,0:07:34.18,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,The same with Mashiro-kun's drawings.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.84,0:07:38.00,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,These drawings are very high quality. They pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.00,0:07:40.61,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,But as for something that surpasses my advice...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.61,0:07:42.65,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,If you came up with something people couldn't ask for,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.65,0:07:44.52,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,that no one could imitate, it'd be perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.21,0:07:51.47,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe I'm setting the bar too high, but please think of it as a compliment that I'm asking this much of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.47,0:07:51.86,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.96,0:07:55.32,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Anyhow, I'll send this in for Golden Future.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.09,0:08:00.70,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I was really surprised that Hattori-san said we could draw mainstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.09,0:08:03.75,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It's got me pretty fired up. Feels like we can do it, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.75,0:08:09.09,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Really? I feel like we were taken in a little. He said it was good, but that it didn't really shine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.91,0:08:10.59,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Shine?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.35,0:08:14.37,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,He said he'd submit it for Golden Future,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.06,0:08:21.02,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,but it sounds like you have to do something that really shocks the editor to be number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.02,0:08:23.53,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,500)}A long time ago, my uncle said the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.20,0:08:27.19,Main,Kawaguchi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There are lots of people that can win awards and debut.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.19,0:08:29.21,Main,Kawaguchi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The real problem comes after that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.21,0:08:32.74,Main,Kawaguchi,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,500)\i1}Those that can make it to serialization are only one out of a few dozen.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.95,0:08:37.95,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It's already hard to be happy about having an entry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.49,0:08:39.83,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be number one and get serialized...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.55,0:08:42.29,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Popular... Popular...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.92,0:08:46.75,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna be popular!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.29,0:08:46.75,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Y–You're embarrassing me, stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.29,0:08:50.92,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for coming all the way here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.92,0:08:52.70,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's Shimoyama-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.70,0:08:54.20,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, he quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.20,0:08:54.93,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,He quit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.19,0:08:59.38,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, the drawings are going fine,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.38,0:09:04.17,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,but under these conditions, I'd appreciate another assistant or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.17,0:09:04.85,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.74,0:09:08.90,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma-kun, I'm here to pick up the manuscript.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.90,0:09:11.27,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.27,0:09:13.57,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,How's Ashirogi-sensei doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.57,0:09:17.73,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Uh, I think they submitted something for the Golden Future Cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.73,0:09:20.26,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that one where they compete?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.26,0:09:21.18,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.18,0:09:23.16,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,They'll have a one-shot running, I'm looking forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.82,0:09:26.22,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Ashirogi-sensei will be number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.22,0:09:28.21,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Crow!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.35,0:09:31.61,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,What? It's not even being entered?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.61,0:09:35.04,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's unfortunate, but that's the feedback I got.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.04,0:09:35.80,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.24,0:09:41.97,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Not only is it not going to be in Golden Future,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.97,0:09:44.48,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,but as it stands, even if it were sent in for the summer NEXT!,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.48,0:09:45.68,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,they said it probably wouldn't do well there either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.47,0:09:48.77,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe mainstream is impossible for us after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.34,0:09:52.27,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who said we had to do mainstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.74,0:09:57.32,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I can't make stories like you, Shuujin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.32,0:09:58.88,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,We should just do the stories you want to—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.88,0:10:00.44,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say stuff like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.44,0:10:03.65,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I said I wanted to aim for the top by doing mainstream too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.33,0:10:07.62,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,To get a call like this, today of all days... {QC: Comma}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.62,0:10:10.60,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,We won't be able to enjoy Azuki's appearance in the anime. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.60,0:10:16.63,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Wh–What's going on? Even though I'm so depressed, I'm actually getting really excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.90,0:10:25.14,Main,Anime,0000,0000,0000,,Sei Visual Gakuin Koutou Bu!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.53,0:10:26.64,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It's starting!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.36,0:10:30.02,Main,Anime,0000,0000,0000,,We...{KmE: This line wasn't in the translation}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.35,0:10:32.56,Main,Anime,0000,0000,0000,,We are saints! {We are seijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.93,0:10:37.55,Main,Anime,0000,0000,0000,,A new excitement is awakening in my heart. {atarashii tokimeki ga mezametekuru}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.55,0:10:41.11,Main,Anime,0000,0000,0000,,If we have a rendezvous, then yes, {machiawaseshite jya iru nara sou}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.69,0:10:43.88,Main,Anime,0000,0000,0000,,your heart is... {kimi no haato...}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.60,0:10:47.55,Main,Lady,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, everyone, take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.55,0:10:50.11,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's almost over already?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.11,0:10:51.97,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Is Azuki really in this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.97,0:10:55.18,Main,Azuki,0000,0000,0000,,U–Um, senpai..
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.18,0:10:56.55,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,There she is! Saotomeji Reika!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.63,0:11:01.01,Main,Azuki,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since... I came to this school, senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.38,0:11:03.93,Main,Azuki,0000,0000,0000,,I–I've liked you, Elina-senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.35,0:11:07.26,Main,Elina,0000,0000,0000,,All the new students say that to me. {This is barely audible but it matches the manga.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.62,0:11:06.13,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Likes her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.13,0:11:07.26,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.26,0:11:08.47,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this charge between them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.47,0:11:09.31,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, Shuujin!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.80,0:11:11.69,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, s–sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.11,0:11:13.35,Main,Elina,0000,0000,0000,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.05,0:11:20.36,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,So in the end, Azuki only had four lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.36,0:11:23.58,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,But she was a lot better than I'd expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.58,0:11:24.74,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Azuki...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{The ED song here's honestly inaudible. A CD of it comes out in like a month,there aren't any lyrics online, I checked. The little message on the bottom's irrelevant.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.04,0:11:29.62,Main,Ootsuki,0000,0000,0000,,This is the actress who plays Ijyuuniin Elina, Ootsukina Nanami. {The rest of what she's saying is inaudible and doesn't match the manga.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.62,0:11:30.93,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It's Azuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.93,0:11:32.67,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Aw man, they're showing her on-screen!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.64,0:11:38.41,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if she's embarrassed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.41,0:11:40.33,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Being shown on TV in cosplay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.33,0:11:42.51,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,No, Azuki's the same as us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.70,0:11:45.76,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,She's determined to move forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.38,0:11:47.79,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,We can't lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.79,0:11:49.18,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Azuki's going to keep doing her best from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.21,0:11:53.54,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,We can't get depressed over something like being rejected!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.54,0:11:57.94,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Y–Yeah. You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.87,0:12:03.71,Main,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Tsuda.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.71,0:12:04.85,Main,Tsuda,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.85,0:12:05.72,Main,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Segawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.72,0:12:06.70,Main,Segawa,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.70,0:12:07.74,Main,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.92,0:12:10.08,Main,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Is Takagi absent?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.97,0:12:11.92,Main,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Takahashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.92,0:12:12.54,Main,Takahashi,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.03,0:12:27.56,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Nice weather, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.16,0:12:33.65,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Your cell phone's ringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.15,0:12:39.15,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.68,0:12:42.44,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Hearing you were rejected must've been a shock, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.97,0:12:43.91,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.05,0:12:46.36,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.36,0:12:46.99,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.55,0:12:49.21,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,You must feel frustrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.21,0:12:50.12,Main,Ashirogi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.12,0:12:51.62,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.65,0:12:56.19,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Your name is in this envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.19,0:12:59.02,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Though the candidates for the Golden Future Cup got sent around to the higher ups,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.02,0:13:00.05,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,the people on this read it and wrote their critiques of it. {QC: "these people critiqued it."}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.45,0:13:01.68,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Give it a read.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.63,0:13:33.27,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Th–That's it. I can't read anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.27,0:13:33.83,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Shuujin...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.37,0:13:38.19,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori-san, you didn't write these yourself, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.21,0:13:40.59,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't do something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.86,0:14:07.19,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I really didn't think the editorial department was expecting so much from us,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.19,0:14:09.11,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,saying we show promise and everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.59,0:14:11.45,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I was surprised too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.33,0:14:15.75,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Though it actually made me feel pressured to write a good piece next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.25,0:14:19.16,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,But that Miyoshi sure is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.16,0:14:19.92,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.72,0:14:25.71,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday when I got home, I checked how many newcomers were closer to serialization than us,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.55,0:14:28.50,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,and there were at least fifteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.50,0:14:29.63,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.63,0:14:35.01,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much they expect of us, all we've done is run in NEXT! once.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.57,0:14:37.37,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we've got some hard work ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.37,0:14:39.69,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,He said your drawings were high quality,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.01,0:14:42.29,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,so I guess now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.29,0:14:44.15,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,400)}I need to focus on my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.78,0:14:48.24,Main,Someone,0000,0000,0000,,Fifteen to two. Group three wins!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.62,0:14:50.79,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Phew, it's finally over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.79,0:14:51.32,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.81,0:14:53.66,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,What about what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.04,0:14:55.79,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,You were watching me the whole time, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.17,0:14:58.00,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I saw your tits bouncing all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.11,0:15:00.90,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Again with that total pervert stuff?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.90,0:15:02.04,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It was a joke...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.00,0:15:04.25,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Look, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.82,0:15:07.43,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It's true, she's in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.43,0:15:09.88,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Anticipated beautiful girls of the seiyuu world? 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.88,0:15:12.34,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,She's on the business office's homepage too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.34,0:15:14.36,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Miho's school doesn't allow part time-jobs,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.36,0:15:14.93,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,so she got in trouble over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.80,0:15:18.39,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I got an email from her saying, "Since I've been such a diligent student, they let me off the hook!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.84,0:15:22.15,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Apparently they said they'll cooperate as long as she puts her schoolwork first.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.15,0:15:24.31,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,It must be nice to be serious and cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.10,0:15:28.82,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Miyoshi, did you come here just to show us this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.76,0:15:31.05,Main,Miyoshi,0000,0000,0000,,I have an announcement.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.05,0:15:32.28,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Announcement?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.28,0:15:34.66,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to you, I too have chosen a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.66,0:15:35.93,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.93,0:15:36.80,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.50,0:15:39.12,Main,Miyoshi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to be a writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.76,0:15:40.37,Main,Ashirogi,0000,0000,0000,,Writer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.30,0:15:44.59,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Miho is a seiyuu... Takagi and Mashiro are mangakas...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.59,0:15:48.36,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I figured that I want to stand on the same level as all of you, so I chose writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.36,0:15:50.72,Main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What a shallow thought process...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.52,0:15:53.86,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,But I think I'll do cell phone novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.86,0:15:55.43,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Lots of companies are taking them on the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.43,0:15:57.16,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,What're you gonna write?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.16,0:15:58.39,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,A romance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.39,0:15:59.52,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Modeled after Miho and Mashiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.66,0:16:03.44,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I'm gonna change it from mangaka and seiyuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.44,0:16:04.77,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make it a novelist and an actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.77,0:16:06.96,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll change the anime adaptation and heroine parts
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.96,0:16:09.05,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,to a live-action drama adaptation and lead actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.05,0:16:10.11,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,That could be interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.63,0:16:11.98,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I know, right? {This is said under Saiko's line.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.11,0:16:11.98,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What the hell are they doing?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.98,0:16:15.01,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,So Takagi, could you help me out a little with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.01,0:16:18.99,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,In exchange, I'll help you write girls' emotions for your manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.99,0:16:24.42,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Hm... Well, for what I'm writing now, I will be needing a heroine...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.42,0:16:27.70,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,1700)}Yay! Then it's settled!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.93,0:16:31.70,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I understand your desire to have a dream too, Miyoshi,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.70,0:16:34.17,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,but honestly I don't want you interfering with our manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.17,0:16:35.85,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Eh, why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.85,0:16:38.05,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna need girl's emotions too, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.05,0:16:41.27,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It's shounen manga, we can just make it a boy's idealized version of a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.80,0:16:42.84,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.84,0:16:44.77,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,But Takagi is the one coming up with the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.02,0:16:49.72,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I've got some of my writing stored on my cell phone. Could you take a look at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.72,0:16:50.19,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Shuujin.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.63,0:16:53.61,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,These plans are all by the book, none of them are original.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.63,0:16:59.45,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,They're not boring, but they feel the same as "Angel Days" that we submitted for the Golden Future Cup. {Yes, he uses a different title here. Apparently they changed it off screen.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.16,0:17:03.54,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Unless we come up with something that'll stand out, I think we'll just get the same result.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.99,0:17:05.05,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.72,0:17:10.07,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that all mainstream stories I write feel similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.07,0:17:13.82,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I've been too focused on what Hattori-san told us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.82,0:17:16.26,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps I'll try to work on it a little more.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.62,0:17:29.40,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Saikou.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.40,0:17:32.22,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I can keep doing this the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.22,0:17:33.08,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,You can't?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.08,0:17:37.13,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It's like I'm forcing myself to think up plans every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.13,0:17:39.69,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,In order to force things to move when they won't,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.69,0:17:42.12,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I keep thinking of original setups to the stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.92,0:17:45.99,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,But I really don't think that'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.99,0:17:47.87,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Unless I can come up with characters that make me say "This is it!", then it's not good enough. {QC: Shorten}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.37,0:17:51.07,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Like Eiji said, characters that move by themselves, and that you want to see move.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.07,0:17:56.05,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,If that comes to me, I think I'll be able to write something different than what we've done up until now,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.05,0:17:58.64,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,something that really stands out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.43,0:18:04.23,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,And though I don't know how to get that yet, I'll use my whole summer vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.23,0:18:06.69,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try to come up with it alone, with a little change of pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.34,0:18:09.81,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.83,0:18:12.27,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.27,0:18:16.48,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,300)}No, sometime during summer vacation, I'll write an interesting name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.90,0:18:35.65,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.65,0:18:36.92,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,A work from Mashiro-kun? {qc - referring to work for Mashiro perhaps? As in the job he's offering, 'A job for Mashiro?', not sure if work is actually in the TL though...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.32,0:18:42.77,Main,Aida,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. For the work that won the second place prize in the name category for the last Story King. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.77,0:18:45.22,Main,Aida,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro-kun's artwork is pretty good for a newcomer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.80,0:18:46.70,Main,Aida,0000,0000,0000,,No good? 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.70,0:18:48.75,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't say something so ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.75,0:18:50.34,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Of course he can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.34,0:18:53.11,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Ashirogi Muto is a two-man team.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.11,0:18:54.90,Main,Aida,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.69,0:18:57.56,Main,Aida,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'll ask elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.56,0:18:58.11,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.10,0:19:01.40,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about Mashiro-kun working as an assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.40,0:19:02.70,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.70,0:19:04.43,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,You're not talking about Niizuma-kun, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.43,0:19:11.08,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The mangaka is sixteen, so the older assistants are giving him the cold shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.08,0:19:13.98,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro-kun is younger than him and he's a good artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.98,0:19:16.14,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Even just for summer vacation would be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.14,0:19:20.10,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Ashirogi Muto thinks of Niizuma-kun as a rival.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.10,0:19:21.33,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he'll go for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.33,0:19:23.66,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you just ask, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.66,0:19:27.06,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,At times like this, as fellow editors, we should help each other out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.04,0:19:31.85,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Only if both Takagi-kun and Mashiro-kun agree to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.47,0:19:34.15,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think they will though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.82,0:19:41.03,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.38,0:19:46.29,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.29,0:19:48.66,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first time you've invited me on a date, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.43,0:19:51.33,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.15,0:19:54.20,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,A movie, karaoke, bowling?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.20,0:19:55.09,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Bowling!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.50,0:20:01.76,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shuujin didn't come today either.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.76,0:20:04.84,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He hasn't contacted me once since summer vacation started.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.93,0:20:09.06,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I guess mainstream really is difficult.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.78,0:20:11.32,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,That was fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.32,0:20:13.19,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,You got over two hundred, that's incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.84,0:20:18.07,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you managed to get a hundred yourself didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.07,0:20:19.57,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't really trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.26,0:20:22.04,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna do karaoke next.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.04,0:20:22.71,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.71,0:20:24.34,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.34,0:20:25.78,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry, my phone's ringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.95,0:20:28.89,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.89,0:20:29.58,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,It's Hattori.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.05,0:20:31.34,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Is the name coming along?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.34,0:20:37.28,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, well, uh... I'm writing some, but I haven't been coming up with anything that Mashiro is happy with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.28,0:20:38.42,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.42,0:20:41.67,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I'm calling to ask if Mashiro could work as an assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.06,0:20:43.44,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.44,0:20:48.01,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,For something like this, I figured I should ask you first before asking Mashiro-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.89,0:20:49.89,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.66,0:20:55.43,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Um... The truth is, I'm sort of struggling right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.43,0:20:57.36,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I can't think of anything that's really "it."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.27,0:21:01.66,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,So, I've been keeping Mashiro waiting the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.66,0:21:03.49,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,And I really don't have any excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.67,0:21:08.08,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,That's why if Mashiro says he'll go, I won't stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.92,0:21:09.87,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.30,0:21:13.85,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Me, be an assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.85,0:21:16.92,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's fine if it's just for summer vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.92,0:21:18.71,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,But right now, we're trying to get serialized...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.19,0:21:24.47,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi-kun was against it, but he said if you wanted to go, he wouldn't stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.47,0:21:26.06,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi said that? 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.06,0:21:30.43,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. And if you want to go, it's for Niizuma-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.12,0:21:32.25,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1\fad(0,150)}Niizuma Eiji...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.95,0:21:37.23,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Until we get serialized, please continue being serialized and wait for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.23,0:21:38.55,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Roger. {QC: Italics flash back in spite of no echoy sounds?}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.55,0:21:41.89,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,But I may be number one by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.89,0:21:43.60,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, you're not obligated to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.86,0:21:46.55,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I'm personally reluctant about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.55,0:21:48.59,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,but I thought I'd ask, just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.11,0:21:52.91,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I understand, I'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.15,0:21:56.13,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro would be an assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.13,0:21:57.87,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he'd be helping out another mangaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.68,0:22:01.21,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you two make up Ashirogi Muto?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.21,0:22:02.71,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault for keeping him waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.59,0:22:07.38,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I'm the one who invited him to become a mangaka in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.33,0:22:12.11,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,So, let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.86,0:22:14.10,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.01,0:22:18.56,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not... getting in the way, am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.36,0:22:25.79,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I go to Eiji's place, I might pick up something.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.79,0:22:28.40,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's for Shuujin's sake too, since he's struggling with the name!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.97,0:24:17.72,Main,Ootsukina,0000,0000,0000,,This is the actress who plays Ijyuuniin Elina, Ootsuki Nanami.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.72,0:24:19.96,Main,Azuki,0000,0000,0000,,I play the role of Saotomeji Reika, my name is Azuki Miho.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.96,0:24:22.10,Main,Ootsukina,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, on the next Sei Visua—
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.74,0:24:23.38,Main,Azuki,0000,0000,0000,,That's not right! Nanami-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.38,0:24:25.49,Main,Ootsuki,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Goblin and Kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.49,0:24:28.35,Main,Ootsuki,0000,0000,0000,,If a dream is conceited it won't come true!
